This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a new learning-based inference and decision strategy for deep neural networks. It also discusses the lack of robustness and interpretability in deep learning, which are common concerns in the field of machine learning. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on several datasets, which is a common practice in the machine learning community. 

The paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it discusses the limitations of deep learning and proposes a new algorithm to address these limitations. 

Furthermore, the paper could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as image recognition is mentioned as one of the innovative applications of deep learning. 

The paper also discusses the vulnerability of deep learning to adversarial inputs, which could place it under the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for deep learning, which could also place it under the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
